{"author":"Michael Giver","data":{"body":"Shipped: committed a3952f4f, pushed, PR #761 open against main (https://github.com/navapbc/oscer/pull/761).\n\nCORRECTION to the earlier forward note (#3): the flat `exclusions_and_exceptions` verified-boolean array was RedMane's initial proposal and is NOT the direction. It can't support the rules OSCER must implement — per Jeff (2026-07-07), an exclusion active only during the lookback becomes a mandatory exception (plus 12-mo postpartum windows), so OSCER makes the time-based judgment and needs per-exemption date context, not flat booleans. Compute-vs-receive resolves toward OSCER computes. So for the future adapter: expect richer/dated exemption input, not a flat boolean array; the return-best selection built here is the durable core the exception band + data-source ordering extend. (Naming-reconciliation + verification_status notes from #1/#2 still stand.)"},"env_id":"7fda8af9-5f39-45e1-9caf-59ffda62ec19","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783545148057936001,"uuid":"f35b083a-da48-46cc-9f61-3306bc1a8665"}